<doc>
  <member name="DISK_GROW_PARTITION">
    <summary>
      <para>Contains information used to increase the size of a partition.This structure is used by the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/api/winioctl/ni-winioctl-ioctl_disk_grow_partition">IOCTL_DISK_GROW_PARTITION</a> control code.</para>
    </summary>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/api/winioctl/ni-winioctl-ioctl_disk_grow_partition">IOCTL_DISK_GROW_PARTITION</seealso>
    <seealso cref="LARGE_INTEGER" />
  </member>
  <member name="DISK_GROW_PARTITION.PartitionNumber">
    <summary>
      <para>The identifier of the partition to be enlarged.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DISK_GROW_PARTITION.BytesToGrow">
    <summary>
      <para>The number of bytes by which the partition is to be enlarged (positive value) or reduced (negative value). Note that this value is not the new size of the partition.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>